,Recommended,319140,29794770,Posted: 8 February,all,Bl0rch,"This was probably one of the most ""Retro"" feeling games I've played in a long time. It's soundtrack reminds me a lot of Metroid and LifeForce/Gradius era games. If you were ever a fan of the NES games like those, this harkens back quite nicely.It's difficult, yet not unforgiving. The controls are smooth, but also take some getting used to.The short list of the good/bad:+Great music+Fluid controls+Cool powerups+Fun boss fights (but they could be better)+Boss checkpoints+Configurable weapon upgrade loadouts - you can choose where you put your gun points and you can rearrange them for free whenever, saved with 3 presets.+Plane shift + run + rocket = <3-If you die while exploring, unless you hit a checkpoint (boss chamber), you're going back. And it could mean the beginning of the map.-All the bosses are the ""same"" - relatively same pattern and same form, not really a whole lot to them once you learn the patterns. fun to play them, but could be better-health pickups are almost non-existent. You can find them from special enemies right before a boss, and hidden in walls, but there's not much else -- so don't get hit!-it's shortIt might seem like a balanced list of good and bad, but the bad are really just aspects of the game that I personally didn't care for -- those seeking a challenge will welcome it.For the controls, the jump height is fixed -- tap or hold the button, you jump the same. It's not so much a problem, but it can be tricky to avoid certain enemies if they aren't at the apex of your jump when you need to hit them.It feels like you're sliding on ice when you jump, but the platforming is pretty simple, so it's not a big deal. It can be meddlesome when you need to avoid enemies, but you can kill most everything.The game is sort of linear, in that you uncover parts of the map that are accessible each time you get a power, but you have to remember all those little places you might have forgotten to check in order to come back later -- hello Metroid.The game is rather short. I completed it in a few hours, without getting 100% of the map/items (I got all the gun powerups, missing about half the health ones).I feel like it could be one you could replay over again to see if you can nab all the achievements or whatnot, but i thought it was extremely worth it."
