,Recommended,319140,23092484,"Posted: 19 May, 2016",all,jsabsd,"I originally wrote a review of this that was brief and a bit hasty. I stand by my complaint, but I feel I can give it a bit more direction.The downsides:* The jump height is fixed. No feathering to shoot the badies. This is a gross oversight and not in line with classic NES style.* Slop in the controls. Not much, but enough to be frustrating. Platforming will just make you angry at the start.* The very first boss is absolutley unforgiving. They are all hard, but the first one is so outright unfair that it led to my initial bad review.* Boss methods are sometimes unclear, leaving you to do random things until something inexplicably changes. Good luck surviving through this. Thankfully, most of the boss behavior is random so he may not even do it next round.* The character's power is quadratic. As you gain more Health and more Gun, you quickly find the challenge taper off.* Some enemies are tedious to kill, not actually hard. There will be a pattern to learn, but do I really need to do it ten times to kill one thing?The upsides:* Challenging, but doable. Bosses require reflexes and patience. It's a difficult mix to master.* Graphics are fantastic. It feels like the love child of my NES favorites Blaster Master and Metroid.* Music is great. (I'm biased, there's a nod to David Bowie on the soundtrack. Instant win.)So with more negative points than positive ones, why am I changing this to recommend? Firstly, because there is no neutral, which is what I really feel it should be. This game is not for everyone, chiefly because the challenge is just too high at the start. With limited space to explore until you down that first boss, the gameplay value becomes about 5 minutes if you cannot proceed.A couple of things that would fix it:* Feathering. Many enemies need a mini-jump to line up the shot. Let us control our jumps. This actually matters.* Difficulty setting. A novice mode in which the bosses movements aren't quite so quick. Also opens the door for hard (bosses have twice the HP) and nightmare (bosses have twice the HP and faster reaction times). Think about it.In the end, I am recommending the game. It's just a weak recommendation, with the caveat that if you are really easily frustrated, you might want to sit this one out (at least until it has a difficulty option)."
