,Recommended,319140,17574849,"Posted: 16 August, 2015",all,Siege,"Picked this up for about $4 on the latest Digital Devolver sale.Pros:Tight, responsive controls.The in-game map is a solid clone of Super Metroid's map.The weapon upgrade system encourages experimentation and has multiple setups so you can quickly swap between the three options depending on the situation.The game doesn't outstay its welcome. If doubled in length, the game would have worn thin.Cons:No controls for cycling weapons and solar flare, requiring the player to access the menu to change.Two of the weapon upgrades are pretty useless. The game was completeable without shot speed or spread. Wave, Power, and rapid fire were sufficient.Bosses are palette swaps, each adding on one new ability along with the previous bosses.The four worlds are small, and nondistinct outside of color.Enemies are simple, and mostly uninteresting.The game is completable in part of an afternoon. A slightly longer end-game to play with all of the acquired abilities in concert would have been welcome."
