,Recommended,319140,18807094,"Posted: 31 October, 2015",all,Argoth,"IntroductionA short but sweet homage and excellent rendition of not only Metroid, but an underrated era of 2D games that existed during the tragically short GBA era of gaming history.MechanicsPrecise and satisfying, the simple controls are easy to learn and satisfying to execute. Several types of enemies and varied bosses to fight, in tough but fair bouts that feel rewarding due to how excellently the physics are implemented. Controller implementation is a bit lacking.GraphicsPerfectly recreates the look and feel of the GBA era of video games. The sprite art is self limited to capture the 16 bit look, but still has a modern flair that looks beautiful. Many homages to Metroid enemies and items, faithfully recreated for nostalgic value.SoundThe music does not capture the same effortless atmosphere and mood of the Metroid series, but is still of high quality. All sound effects have a satisfying punch to them and help to carry the experience forward.ConclusionIf you ever owned a handheld Nintendo system, were ever a fan of Metroid, or indeed enjoy any short and sweet video game experience, I highly recommend this game."
