76561197974749063,Recommended,319140,31789284,Posted: 16 May,all,Muig,"MINI METROIDI got this for £0.69 in a Steam sale, and thoroughly enjoyed it.  It's a Mini version of Metroid: short, simplified, relatively easy, with miniaturised graphics.  The acid-coloured, cute look of the game was a big part of the appeal for me; judge for yourself from the screenshots.If there was a story, I've forgotten it already - but the mission follows the Metroid template: find items that give you special powers which give you access to new parts of the map.  The weapon system is quite good: you allocate points to customise your gunfire, changing power, speed, pattern, etc.  I found that the parabola pattern was the best all-rounder.There is the usual Metroid backtracking through parts of the map, for example when you decide you need more health or gun collectibles to defeat a boss, but I didn't find this too troublesome- the maps are quite small, and (most) of the enemies are not hard to beat once you've figured them out.A fairly novel feature to the game is the ability to shift into the background layer at times.  This plays a part in the gameplay here and there, and it's quite an enjoyable, cool little addition.Some reviewers have criticised the lack of save points: you have to make it back to your ship to save.  I was irritated by this at first myself, but once you know you can't just rush carelessly through a map, it adds to the challenge and tension of the game.  Can't be bad.CONS:Though I really liked the sound effects, I can't say the same for the music.  I've got a lot of time for chiptunes, but the music here was too basic and repetitive and became grating.Having to go to the menu to select a different weapon seemed unnecessary.  Since the game  has Xbox controller support, why not allow weapon selection using the shoulder buttons?COMPARISONS:I tried Environmental Station Alpha before this, which appears to have been better-received, but I didn't like it.  The music is much better, but the graphics are too tiny and pixelated even for me, and the gameplay was less accessible.I've also purchased Mutant Mudds off the back of this- because it has the same developer- but although it again seems to have been better-received, I'm finding it inferior so far.  Slow, a bit clunky and too simplistic.CONCLUSION:All in all, I'd heartily recommend this game if you're looking for a slice of retro Metroid fun.  Some reviewers here feel short-changed by the short length I think,  but at the sort of discount I got it's a no-brainer."
